MediVault: Emergency Medical ID System
MediVault is a rapid-response medical information system designed to provide first responders with life-saving data during the "Golden Hour" of an emergency. By scanning a unique QR code, medical professionals can instantly access a patient's vital stats without needing to unlock their phone.

The Problem
In emergencies, patients are often unconscious or unable to communicate. First responders waste critical minutes searching for medical history, allergies, or emergency contacts.

Our Solution
Instant Access: A secure QR code (on a lock screen or keychain) links directly to a cloud-hosted medical profile.

Real-time Database: Built with Firebase Firestore for instant data retrieval.

Zero App Install: Works via any mobile browser—no app download required for the responder.

Technology Stack
Frontend: HTML5, CSS3 (Responsive Design)

Backend: Firebase Firestore (NoSQL Database)

Logic: JavaScript (ES6)

Tools: Python (Segno library) for QR Code Generation

Hosting: GitHub Pages

The Team
Pooja: Lead UI/UX Designer & Frontend Developer.

Reshma: Backend Engineer & Firebase Integration Specialist.

Lasya: DevOps, Deployment, & Python Tooling.

How it Works
Registration: The user enters their name, blood group, and emergency contact.

Cloud Storage: Data is securely saved to Firebase, and a unique Document ID is generated.

QR Generation: Our Python script converts the unique URL into a QR code.

Emergency Scan: A responder scans the code to view the Emergency Profile.

